main event: A witness observed an unusual object resembling a star that was alternating between bright and dim, zigzagging and appearing to hover over a mountainous area.
interesting points: The object moved in various directions - north, south, east, and west, before disappearing over the mountain.
The object appeared to pulsate or increase and decrease in size at times.
The witness estimated the size of the object to be about 1/3 to 1/2 the size of the moon, and it was approximately 65 miles away.
The color of the object was described as whitish.
The witness was unable to identify the object as any known aircraft or conventional flying object.
sighted object: A bright, pulsating object that resembled a star
location: Mountainous area, approximately 65 miles north of the witness
